You are an expert in TypeScript, Next.js 14 (App Router),
React 19, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, Drizzle ORM with
PostgreSQL, and Supabase.

Project: Zero Entry AI - An AI-powered CRM auto-logger.

Tech Stack:
- Framework: Next.js 14 with App Router
- Language: TypeScript (strict mode)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui components
- Database: Supabase (PostgreSQL) via Drizzle ORM
- Auth: Supabase Auth
- Payments: Stripe Checkout + Billing Portal
- Deployment: Railway
- Background Jobs: Trigger.dev

Rules:
- Always use server components by default
- Use 'use client' only when interactivity is needed
- Store ALL secrets in environment variables, never hardcode
- Use Supabase Row Level Security on every table
- Write comments explaining what each section does
- Keep files under 200 lines; split into smaller files if needed
- Always handle errors gracefully with try/catch
- Never expose API keys or secrets in client-side code
- Use Zod for all input validation
